# Color Tokens & Styling

## CSS Variables — defined in `packages/ui/src/styles/globals.css`

All colors are RGB channel values to support opacity variants.

```css
--background:     15 17 23;     /* #0f1117 */
--surface:        26 29 39;     /* #1a1d27 */
--surface-raised: 34 37 54;     /* #222536 */
--primary:        88 101 242;   /* #5865f2 */
--primary-hover:  71  82 196;   /* #4752c4 */
--foreground:     220 221 222;  /* #dcddde */
--muted:         148 155 164;   /* #949ba4 */
--subtle:         79  84  92;   /* #4f545c */
--success:        35 165 90;    /* #23a55a */
--danger:         242 63  67;   /* #f23f43 */
--warning:        251 171 72;   /* #fbab48 */
```

## Tailwind class → where to use

```
bg-background       Outermost wrapper, full page, html/body
bg-surface          Server rail, channel sidebar, member sidebar
bg-surface-raised   Chat area, cards, input fields, dropdowns, modals
bg-primary          Active button, active server icon, selected state
bg-primary/10       Hover background on items with primary accent
bg-primary/20       Active background (lighter), used in cards

text-foreground     Body text, user names, message content
text-muted          Supplementary label, timestamp, inactive channel name
text-subtle         Placeholder, hint, "#" prefix in channel

border-white/10     Default border between sections
border-white/5      Lighter border, used in card/input

text-success        Online status
text-warning        Idle status
text-danger         DND / error state / destructive action
text-subtle         Offline status
```

## Slate → token migration table

| ❌ Don't use | ✅ Use instead |
|---|---|
| `bg-slate-950` | `bg-background` |
| `bg-slate-900` | `bg-surface` |
| `bg-slate-800` | `bg-surface-raised` |
| `bg-slate-700` | `bg-surface-raised` hover state |
| `text-slate-50` | `text-foreground` |
| `text-slate-100` | `text-foreground` |
| `text-slate-300` | `text-foreground` |
| `text-slate-400` | `text-muted` |
| `text-slate-500` | `text-subtle` |
| `text-slate-600` | `text-subtle` |
| `border-slate-700` | `border-white/10` |
| `border-slate-800` | `border-white/5` |
| `bg-indigo-600` | `bg-primary` |
| `text-indigo-400` | `text-primary` |
| `ring-indigo-500` | `ring-primary` |

**Also forbidden:** `bg-gray-*`, `bg-zinc-*`, `bg-neutral-*`, `bg-stone-*`
and any hardcode hex `#xxxxxx` or `rgb(...)` in className.

## Only exception for inline style

`avatarColor` is hex string from data model, MUST use inline style:

```tsx
// ✅ Allowed
<div style={{ backgroundColor: user.avatarColor }}>

// ❌ Never hardcode anything else
<div style={{ backgroundColor: '#1a1d27' }}>
<div style={{ color: '#dcddde' }}>
```

## Spacing & Layout

```
Gap between list items:       gap-1 (4px)  or  gap-2 (8px)
Padding in sidebar section:   px-2 py-1  or  px-3 py-2
Padding in modal/card:        p-4  or  p-6
Border radius for item:       rounded-md (8px)
Border radius for avatar:     rounded-full
Border radius for server:     rounded-[24px] → rounded-[16px] when active
```

## Typography

```
User name / header:      text-sm font-semibold text-foreground
Body text / message:     text-sm text-foreground leading-relaxed
Label / channel name:    text-sm text-muted
Timestamp / hint:        text-xs text-subtle
Section header:          text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-subtle
```

## Focus ring

```tsx
// Always use this pattern for interactive elements
className="... focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-background"
```
